# FitOwn — Source of Truth

This repo is **FitOwn (MASGARTI Fit Tech)** POC v0.1. Follow project docs before acting.

## Mandatory read order

1. @docs/planning/README.md — planning index (start here)
2. Matching module plan: @docs/planning/plans/ — one file per feature area
3. Scope: @docs/planning/PRODUCT.md
4. Stack: @docs/planning/TECH_STACK.md (pnpm, Expo, Supabase)
5. Phases: @docs/planning/IMPLEMENTATION_ROADMAP.md

Root agent guide: @AGENTS.md

## Project skills (.cursor/skills/)

| Skill | When |
|-------|------|
| `fitown-project` | Product context, POC boundaries |
| `fitown-mobile-standards` | Code in apps/mobile or packages |
| `fitown-figma-mobile` | Figma → React Native UI |
| `fitown-supabase-migrations` | SQL migrations, schema, `pnpm db:migrate` — **not** user-supabase MCP |

For Figma MCP: load `figma-use` before `use_figma`.

## Hard constraints

- **pnpm only** — not npm or yarn
- **POC scope only** — defer wearables, AI, CV, blockchain (PRODUCT.md §4.2)
- **Plans before code** — read the module plan file before implementing its features
- **Data ownership** — client owns data; trainer view is read-only
- **Figma icons** — MCP exports are often SVG saved as `.png`; they render blank with `expo-image`. Use `react-native-svg` in `components/icons/`. Verify with `file <path>`. See @.cursor/skills/fitown-figma-mobile/references/asset-export.md
